A massive blue elephant, weathered and cracked like ancient stone, standing alone in a vast desert landscape at dusk. The elephant's body shows visible fractures with pieces crumbling away, revealing intricate mechanical gears and circuits beneath the surface. Vultures circle overhead in a burnt orange sky. In the distance, sleek silver gazelles made of polished chrome race toward the horizon, representing agile competitors. The elephant's trunk is raised defiantly despite its deteriorating state. Scattered around its feet are fossilized computer parts half-buried in sand dunes. The scene conveys both former majesty and inevitable decline. Photorealistic style with dramatic golden hour lighting casting long shadows across the rippled sand. Cinematic composition with the elephant positioned slightly off-center, emphasizing isolation and scale against the endless desert expanse.
